main event: An Air Intelligence Information Report concerning an unidentified flying object sighting in Platteville, Wisconsin, on June 23, 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as a round type, and it was observed flying in a north-west direction., The sighting occurred at approximately 10:50 P.M., and the altitude was estimated at 20,000 feet., The weather was clear, but lightning was visible in the western sky due to an incoming cold front., There is no information about the observer and no physical evidence of the sighting., The report lacks any identification or interrogation action due to a delay in reporting.
witness description: No knowledge of the observer, classified as G-2
